# Times Product Language (TPL) Design Tokens

TPL design tokens are the foundation of our design system, providing consistent styling across iOS applications. This document outlines the available tokens and their usage.

## Color Tokens

TPL provides color tokens in three main categories, each supporting light and dark themes. Colors can be accessed through SwiftUI's `Color` type or as a `ShapeStyle`.

### Content Palette
Note: Do NOT use `contentAccent`

- `contentPrimary` - Primary content color
- `contentPrimaryDim` - Dimmed primary content
- `contentSecondary` - Secondary content color
- `contentSecondaryDim` - Dimmed secondary content
- `contentBreaking` - Used for breaking news indicators
- `contentNegative` - Used for error states
- `contentPlaceholder` - Placeholder text color
- `contentPositive` - Used for success states

### Stroke Palette
- `strokePrimary` - Primary border color
- `strokeSecondary` - Secondary border color
- `strokeTertiary` - Tertiary border color

### Background Palette
- `backgroundPrimary` - Primary background color
- `backgroundSecondary` - Secondary background color
- `backgroundTertiary` - Tertiary background color
- `backgroundHighlight` - Highlight background color
- `backgroundScrim` - Semi-transparent overlay color

### Color Behaviors
Each color token supports four behavior variants:
- Default: Responds to system light/dark mode
- `AlwaysLight`: Always uses light theme value
- `AlwaysDark`: Always uses dark theme value
- `UserInverse`: Inverts the current theme

## Typography Tokens

TPL typography tokens combine font families, sizes, weights, and line spacing. All typography tokens support Dynamic Type.

### Text Styles
- `text12` through `text20` - For product copy (Franklin Medium)
- `title12` through `title56` - For headings and emphasis (Franklin Semibold)
- `titleKarnak16`, `titleKarnak18` - For sub-brands & newsletters (Karnak Bold)
- `labelRegular`, `labelEmphasis` - For short, contextual text (Franklin Medium/ExtraBold)

### Headline Styles
- `headline16` through `headline28` - General headlines (Cheltenham Book/Medium)
- `headlineNews16` through `headlineNews48` - News headlines (Cheltenham Bold)
- `headlineFeature24` through `headlineFeature56` - Feature headlines (Cheltenham Light/ExtraLight)
- `headlineOpinion18` through `headlineOpinion56` - Opinion headlines (Cheltenham Condensed Bold)

### Body Text
- `body14` through `body20` - Story content (Imperial Regular)

## Spacing Tokens

TPL provides a comprehensive set of spacing tokens for consistent layout metrics.

### Border Widths
- `border1` - 1.00pt
- `border1_5` - 1.50pt
- `border2` - 2.00pt

### Spacing Scale
- `spacing0_5` - 4.00pt
- `spacing1` - 8.00pt
- `spacing1_5` - 12.00pt
- `spacing2` - 16.00pt
- `spacing2_5` - 20.00pt
- `spacing3` - 24.00pt
- `spacing4` - 32.00pt
- `spacing5` - 40.00pt
- `spacing6` - 48.00pt
- `spacing7` - 56.00pt
- `spacing8` - 64.00pt
- `spacing9` - 72.00pt
- `spacing10` - 80.00pt

## Usage Examples

### SwiftUI Example
```swift
import SwiftUI
import TPL

struct ExampleView: View {
    var body: some View {
        VStack(alignment: .leading) {
            Text("Headline")
                .typography(.tpl.headline24)
                .foregroundColor(.tpl.contentPrimary)
                
            Text("Body text")
                .typography(.tpl.body16)
                .foregroundColor(.tpl.contentSecondary)
        }
        .padding(.tpl.spacing2)
        .background(.tpl.backgroundSecondary)
    }
}
```

### UIKit Example
```swift
import UIKit
import TPL

let label = UILabel()
label.attributedText = "Headline".attributed(.tpl.headline24)
label.textColor = .tpl.contentPrimary
label.backgroundColor = .tpl.backgroundSecondary
```
